Description: Sterling is a practice management and consulting company, devoted to helping professionals build smooth-running, profitable offices.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Sterling is an award-winning practice management and consulting company, devoted to helping professionals build smooth-running, profitable offices. The best and most successful consulting group of its kind, Sterling offers a unique program of training and consulting to help professionals build highly successful practices. Sterling has always played its role on a very large scale. In fact, over the past 36 years, Sterling has trained more than 160,000 professionals and staff in 1,700 cities across all 50 states. In addition, Our team of experts has provided over half a million hours of consulting, apprenticing and coaching to practice owners and their staff. From its headquarters in Glendale, CA, Sterling welcomes thousands of professionals each year, including Dentists, Orthodontists, Accountants, Optometrists, Veterinarians, Physical Therapists, Chiropractors, and Podiatrists. Sterling began in the back office of a dental practice just outside San Francisco in March 1983. By 1985, the company had grown into a multi-million dollar organization delivering practice management seminars across the country. In July 1986, Sterling moved to Glendale, California, where the company expanded even more rapidly. In 1988 Sterling added programs for professional offices of Optometry, Physical Therapy, Veterinarian, Chiropractic, and Podiatric Medicine. Then in 1993, we added CPAs and accounting practices, which has since grown to become one of Sterling’s largest client bases. By 1988, Sterling had earned the #45 spot on Inc. magazine’s list of the 500 fastest-growing, privately-held companies in the U.S. The following year, Sterling again made the Inc. 500 list at #117, joining a very short list of companies to accomplish the feat, not just once, but twice. To accommodate further expansion, in 2007, the company purchased and moved into its own 20,000 square-foot headquarters where it continues to operate today.

Description: Grid Symphony is an award-winning smart power grid and smart building technology company.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Grid Symphony® is an award-winning smart power grid and smart building technology company. It provides Edge™ Solution for Energy Optimization with applications in various areas: 1. Application in Energy Storage Integration, Renewable Power Generation and Microgrid. This software integrates and optimizes multiple sources and sinks, balancing solar/wind or other renewable power generation, grid scale energy storage, power grid capacity and reliability, demand and economics, to ensure maximum benefits for the renewable power producer while satisfying other parties' needs. It enables adaptive control for Microgrid, matching and tuning heterogeneous energy sources (grid, distributed generation such as Solar/Wind, CHP/NG, Diesel generation), energy consumers (curtailable or non-curtailable load), energy storages (batteries), bi-directional EV charging stations and others to achieve reliable, cost-efficient operation of the Microgrid.  2. Application in EV Charging. This software provides intelligent control of EV charging facilities with more than one EV charger in place, in order to minimize load demand and impact to the power grid, while maximizing EV charging capacity and economics. It works for facilities with EV chargers, onsite energy storage, and onsite power generation. The incremental demand peak and associated cost incurred for demand based on EV fleet size with this solution is many times less than the plain vanilla EV charging facilities. 3. Application in Buildings and Health Care Facilities. This software allows building and health care facility managers and operators to not only obtain real time data on energy consumption but also adjust facility behavior based on that data. It brings artificial intelligence to facility management and has self-learning capability that adapts to the facility behavior as it goes along. It provides holistic integration of real-time data from heterogeneous sub-systems, intelligent forecasting and optimization to aid building operation decisions, autonomic capability to actuate building sub-systems such as VFDs through common protocol (such as BACnet or Modbus) as an autopilot, to achieve energy-efficient intelligent building.

Full Description: Aeyrium provides pilots, commercial operators, leasing companies, and repair stations with real-time insight into how their aircraft are being used and maintained. Aeyrium also reduces overhead and eliminates the need for paper-based recordkeeping by converting an Aircraft's Maintenance Logbook history into a tamper-proof system built on blockchain. Pilots, operators, leasers, mechanics—all of them win with Aeyrium.
